Each board of library trustees shall:
Provide for an audit at least annually, by an accountant approved by the State Superintendent of its business and financial transactions and of the accounts of its treasurer;
Make public the results of the annual audit; and
Make an annual report to the county governing body and the State Superintendent on or before November 1 of each year, except that a county having a population of more than 500,000 and having a county library agency as provided by § 23-401(b) of this subtitle shall submit their report by January 1. The report shall show:
The amounts of money received from the library fund and other sources;
The itemized expenses;
The number of books and periodicals the library has;
The results of the annual audit; and
Any other information the Department requires.

Each board of library trustees may:
Accept any gift, grant, or appropriation for library purposes from any person under any appropriate terms and conditions;
Own and dispose of these gifts, grants, and appropriations;
Recommend to the county governing body the acquisition, use, or conveyance of property, for any purpose valid under this subtitle;
Select the location of and approve plans for the erection of library buildings, subject to the approval of the county governing body;
Make contracts for any library service with any person; and
Do anything else necessary for the proper control and development of the library.
